Ing '''Shimla''' {{audio|Shimla.ogg|pronunciation}} {{IPA|[[International Phonetic Alphabet|[ʃɪmla]]]}} ([[Hindi]]: शिमला), a sadiang mayayaus '''Simla''', metung yang lakanbalen king [[Estadu ampong teritoriu ning India|estadu]] ning [[Himachal Pradesh]]. Tungku (capitoliu o cabecera) ne mu naman ning estadu, at metung yang [[w:Municipal corporation|municipal corporation]] kilub ning [[Shimla (distritu)]]<ref name='shimla_distt'>{{cite web}}</ref>. 

Mibulalag yang tungkung pangkaleldo (''summer capital'') ning [[w:British Raj|kapamahalan ning Britania king India]] ing Shimla kanitang 1864. Metung yang taniag a pupuntalan da reng turista, at ausan deng "Queen of Hills" (Reina da reng Talimunduk, bansag a ibat kareng Ingles). Maki kakeuan ya o pulu ning [[pinu]], [[w:Rhododendron|rhododendron]], ampong [[w:oak|robles]] o ''oak'' ing Shimla, a presku neng kaleldo at marimlang maki yelu neng karimlan. Atiu king dakeng pangulu-albugan (''north-west'') da reng kabundukan a [[Himalayas]], at maki tas yang {{convert|2130|m|ft|0}}.  Pikabaluan ya ing lakanbalen kareng kayang gusali king istilung [[w:tudorbethan|tudorbethan]] ampong [[w:Neo Gothic|neo-gothic]]. Makatuglung ya ing Shimla king lakanbalen ning [[Kalka]] kapamilatan ning metung karing makabang dili kareng mitatágan a rutang [[w:Narrow gauge railway|narrow gauge railway]] king India.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.irfca.org/docs/ng-routes.html | title = Narrow Gauge Routes | publisher = IRFCA - The Indian Railways Fan Club | accessdate=2007-05-21}}</ref>. Maki dayu yang 115 km (71.4 miles) ibat king [[Chandigarh]], ing pekamalapit a manimunang lakanbalen, ampong 365 km (226.8 miles) ibat king [[New Delhi]], ing tungku ning bangsa, ing Shimla. 

